"a.厌氧的 【考】 反义词: living in oxygen(生活在氧气中 的); respiration(呼吸) adj. (特指微生物)厌氧的 【记】an非, 不, aero空气－不需空气的－厌氧的 【参】anaerobe(n 厌氧微生物－可在无氧环境下生存的一种有机体) 【反】living in oxygen(活在氧气中的); respiration(n 呼吸); require oxygen(需要氧气的) 【记】an 反 + aer air 反空气→厌氧 anaerobic (adj.)  ""capable of living without oxygen,"" 1879 (as anaerobian; modern form first attested 1884), from French anaérobie, coined 1863 by French bacteriologist Louis Pasteur (1822-1895), from Greek an- ""without"" (see an- (1)) + aer ""air"" (see air (n.1)) + bios ""life"" (see bio-)."
